{"word":"αἶθοψ","slug":"αἶθοψ","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>αἶθοψ</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><el>αἴθω, ὄψ</el>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>fiery-looking</i>, of metal, <i>flashing</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>; of wine, <i>sparkling</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>; of smoke, <i>mixed with flame</i>, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>swart, dark</i>, <b><a href='S:Anthology'>Anth.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a> <i>fiery, keen, eager</i>, <a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>ardens</el>, <b><a href='S:Hesiod'>Hes.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}